<h1>Egg Salad</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>12 hard-boiled eggs  </li>
<li>2/3 cup mayonnaise  </li>
<li>4 tablespoons whole grain mustard  </li>
<li>1/2 teaspoon salt  </li>
<li>1 teaspoon black pepper  </li>
<li>Zest and juice of 1 lemon  </li>
<li>3 teaspoons dried dill, or 3 tablespoons finely diced fresh dill  </li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Finely grate the hard-boiled eggs into a large mixing bowl.  </li>
<li>Add the mayonnaise, mustard, salt, pepper, lemon zest and juice, and dill.  </li>
<li>Mix gently until well combined. Let sit for 5â€“10 minutes if using dried dill, to allow the flavors to meld.  </li>
<li>Serve on toast, in a sandwich, or with your favorite crackers.</li>
</ol>
